I found that this also allowed me to run the test without a race.

It looks like in the two places we call NormalizeURNReferences outside of a test, it's immediately after initializing a new snapshot. If we do the deepcopy inside `NewSnapshot`, that meshes with the name of the method (it's a snapshot!) and I think is logically equivalent to these two lines.

There's one test where we call `NormalizeURNReferences` at the end and verify no error.

```go
// NewSnapshot creates a snapshot from the given arguments.  The resources must be in topologically sorted order.
// This property is not checked; for verification, please refer to the VerifyIntegrity function below.
func NewSnapshot(manifest Manifest, secretsManager secrets.Manager,
	resources []*resource.State, ops []resource.Operation) *Snapshot {

	return &Snapshot{
		Manifest:          deepcopy.Copy(manifest).(Manifest),
		SecretsManager:    deepcopy.Copy(secretsManager).(secrets.Manager),
		Resources:         deepcopy.Copy(resources).([]*resource.State),
		PendingOperations: deepcopy.Copy(ops).([]resource.Operation),
	}
}
```

