In that case, given that the "L", "M" and "H" simply correspond to multiplicative factors 0.75, 1.25 and 1.5 respectively, I could simply do:
```python
class BindiEtAl2014Rhyp(...):
    def __init__(self, stress_drop_scaling=1.0):
        self.stress_drop_scaling = np.log(stress_drop_scaling)

    def get_mean_and_stddevs(...):
        mean, stddevs = super().get_mean_and_stddevs(...)
        return mean + self.stress_drop_scaling, stddevs
```
Thus the factors can be adjusted to whatever the user wishes.

by default a next question for a question is the one defined after it in the questions' array. We don't need to define this`nextQuestion` map unless we have the need to do branching. I understand that this will need a last question that all branches terminates to but this is usually the case in the interactive-flows, you end the questionnaire with a message. For example, in the case you provided it will be something like this:

```
[
     {
         "key": "q1",
         "nextQuestion": {
                  "True": "q2",
                  "False": "q3",
         }
     },
     {
         "key": "q2"
         "defaultNextQuestion": "q4"
     },
     {
         "key": "q3"
     },
     {
         "key": "q4"
         "kind": "info"
         "question": "End of Text 👯👯 "
     }
]
```

