It's somewhat arbitrary but, after pondering different options, I decided to go for this compromise:

* There were several instances of 'CIE-LAB' in `skimage/color/colorconv.py` (before #6688) so I've taken this legacy into account;
* Reference http://www.easyrgb.com/en/math.php hyphenates these colorspace acronyms, so even if we don't follow *exactly* their convention, it gives weight to the possible choice of hyphenating;
* I'd be happy to go the Wikipedia way, but since 'CIE' acts like a prefix, we might as well use a hyphen for the sake of clarity and readability. Likewise, you may write either 'postmodernism' or 'post-modernism' -- both are correct, but 'post-modernism' is more easily parseable at a glance. I try to make it as comfortable as possible for the reader/user and for the future maintainer :slightly_smiling_face:

